RICE PUDDING

3 cups milk			1/2 tsp cinnamon
2 Tbsp cornstarch		1/4 cup raisins, if desired
1/3 cup sugar			1 tsp vanilla
1/2 cup long grain rice, uncooked

Combine milk, cornstarch, and sugar in a large saucepan.  Bring to a
slow boil, stirring constantly.  Add rice.  Cook until thick, stirring
well.  Remove from heat.  Stir in remaining ingredients.  Cool
slightly if serving warm, otherwise cover and chill.


